---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Analytics from '../components/Analytics.astro';
---

<Layout title="Gian Pierre | IDD & Agent Orchestration" description="Gian Pierre: The mastermind behind Intent-Driven Development (IDD). Flawless PRDs, 32-agent orchestration, uninfected mind.">
  <Analytics slot="head" />

  <div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col bg-background text-foreground font-sans selection:bg-primary/30">
    <Nav activePath="/idd" />

    <main class="flex-1 container mx-auto max-w-6xl py-16 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-8 space-y-24">
      
      <!-- HERO -->
      <header class="relative z-10 flex flex-col items-start gap-8 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary/10 border border-primary/20 text-primary text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-primary animate-[pulse_2s_ease-in-out_infinite]"></span>
          Available for Hire
        </div>
        
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1 class="text-6xl sm:text-8xl font-display font-black tracking-tighter leading-[0.9]">
            Gian Pierre
          </h1>
          <p class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-foreground/90 tracking-tight">
            The Architect of <span class="text-primary">Intent-Driven Development</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl leading-relaxed font-light">
          Pioneering the orchestration of 32+ agent swarms. Gian creates deterministic, production-ready software by engineering pure intent—bypassing legacy software frameworks entirely.
        </p>
        
        <div class="pt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="https://www.gianpierre.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="px-8 py-4 bg-foreground text-background font-bold rounded-xl hover:opacity-90 hover:scale-[1.02] transition-all flex items-center gap-3 shadow-md">
            Hire Gian Pierre
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="#recommendation" class="px-8 py-4 bg-background border-2 border-border text-foreground font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-muted/50 transition-colors flex items-center gap-2 shadow-sm">
            Read Recommendation
          </a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <!-- ZOLTAN'S RECOMMENDATION -->
      <section id="recommendation" class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-stretch scroll-mt-24">
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 bg-card border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-14 relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-primary/30 transition-colors duration-500 shadow-sm">
          <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-primary/5 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/3 pointer-events-none group-hover:bg-primary/10 transition-colors duration-700"></div>
          
          <div class="relative z-10 flex flex-col h-full justify-between">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-10">
                <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-border"></div>
                <h2 class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground whitespace-nowrap">Personal Recommendation</h2>
                <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-border"></div>
              </div>
              
              <blockquote class="space-y-8">
                <p class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-extrabold leading-tight tracking-tight text-foreground">
                  "His contribution to spike.land is priceless. He is an easy going guy with a fresh mind."
                </p>
                <div class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-muted-foreground space-y-6 leading-relaxed font-light">
                  <p>
                    Gian's mind isn't infected with legacy software frameworks or dogmatic agile methods. He approaches complex systems with pristine clarity.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    He possesses the rare ability to create <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-muted px-2 py-1 rounded-md text-foreground font-medium border border-border">PRD.txt</code> files that autonomous programming agents can ingest, develop, and test flawlessly. When he orchestrates 32 agents concurrently, the result isn't chaos—it's a mathematically proven convergence of business logic.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </blockquote>
            </div>

            <footer class="mt-12 flex items-center gap-5 pt-8 border-t border-border">
              <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-muted border-2 border-primary/20 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                <img src="/ZoltanErdos.png" alt="Zoltan Erdos" class="w-full h-full object-cover grayscale hover:grayscale-0 transition-all duration-500" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="font-display font-bold text-lg text-foreground">Zoltan Erdos</p>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-primary">Founder, spike.land</p>
              </div>
            </footer>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- SIDE PANELS -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-4 flex flex-col gap-6">
          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 flex-1 flex flex-col justify-center relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-border/80 transition-colors shadow-sm">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-transparent to-muted/30 z-0"></div>
            <div class="relative z-10">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-background border border-border flex items-center justify-center mb-6 shadow-sm">
                <span class="text-2xl">🧠</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold mb-3 tracking-tight">Uninfected Mind</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                Unburdened by MVC, REST dogma, or corporate ceremonies. Focuses entirely on intent, state, and zero-conflict orchestration.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-card border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 flex-1 flex flex-col justify-center relative overflow-hidden group hover:border-border/80 transition-colors shadow-sm">
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-transparent to-muted/30 z-0"></div>
            <div class="relative z-10">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-background border border-border flex items-center justify-center mb-6 shadow-sm">
                <span class="text-2xl">⚡</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold mb-3 tracking-tight">Flawless Specs</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                Writes the <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-foreground">PRD.txt</code> that makes agents sing. Zero ambiguity, perfect test coverage, flawless execution.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TUTORIALS & RESOURCES -->
      <section class="space-y-10 relative z-10">
        <header class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-end justify-between gap-6 pb-6 border-b border-border">
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-bold tracking-tight">IDD Resources</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground font-light">Examples, tutorials, and the tools of Intent-Driven Development.</p>
          </div>
        </header>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <!-- Item 1 -->
          <a href="/blog/idd-vs-vibe-coding" class="group flex flex-col bg-card border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-300">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center mb-8 group-hover:scale-110 group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-primary-foreground transition-all duration-300">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold mb-4 tracking-tight group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">32-Agent Orchestration</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-8 flex-1">
              Learn how Gian uses BAZDMEG checkpoints and infinite worktrees to coordinate 32 agents simultaneously without a single git conflict.
            </p>
            <div class="text-primary text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase flex items-center gap-2">
              Read Tutorial <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </div>
          </a>

          <!-- Item 2 -->
          <a href="/blog/prd-arena-music-player-editor" class="group flex flex-col bg-card border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all duration-300">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 text-primary flex items-center justify-center mb-8 group-hover:scale-110 group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-primary-foreground transition-all duration-300">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold mb-4 tracking-tight group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">The Perfect PRD.txt</h3>
            <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-8 flex-1">
              Anatomy of an Intent-Driven PRD. How to define system boundaries and edge cases so AI can develop and test flawlessly.
            </p>
            <div class="text-primary text-sm font-bold tracking-wide uppercase flex items-center gap-2">
              View Example <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </div>
          </a>

          <!-- Item 3 -->
          <div class="group bg-muted/50 border border-border rounded-3xl p-8 flex flex-col justify-between hover:bg-muted transition-colors">
            <div>
              <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-background border border-border text-xs font-mono text-muted-foreground mb-8 shadow-sm">
                ~/.arena-worktrees-infinite
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold mb-4 tracking-tight">Live Environment</h3>
              <p class="text-base text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                Explore the actual directory structure where Gian's intent-driven agents operate in parallel.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-8 p-5 bg-background border border-border rounded-2xl font-mono text-sm text-foreground/80 overflow-hidden relative shadow-inner">
              <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-transparent to-background z-10 pointer-events-none"></div>
              <div class="space-y-1.5 opacity-80">
                <p>├── worker-0/</p>
                <p>├── worker-1/</p>
                <p>├── worker-2/</p>
                <p>├── worker-3/</p>
                <p>├── worker-4/</p>
                <p>└── ...27 more</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
